{"type":"message","id":"1c59febe","parentId":"3c5da532","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:41:16.544Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Verifying Claude's Role**\n\nI've confirmed that `claude` is installed, and the `coding-agent` skill, which supports `claude`, is present. Now, I'm specifically checking whether a skill dedicated to Claude Code might be absent, potentially causing a functional gap. I'm focusing on whether a special skill is required, or is there a bug with the current setup.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cb1532d810052c05","name":"process","arguments":{"sessionId":"mellow-valley","action":"poll","timeout":30000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":6120,"output":31,"cacheRead":16227,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22378,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775205673005,"responseId":"chatcmpl-3b4c6dbd-5a87-4871-a86c-bf0e5bbaea66"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9446737a","parentId":"1c59febe","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:41:16.562Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_cb1532d810052c05","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"tasks such as mobile game botting or app testing.\n\n### Key Components\n\n1.  **WebDriverAgent (WDA) Customization**:\n    *   Located in `WebDriverAgent.xcodeproj`, `WebDriverAgentLib`, and `WebDriverAgentRunner`.\n    *   Customized with features like OCR engines (`FBOCREngine.mm`), MJPEG server optimizations, and specialized commands (`FBECWDACommands.m`) for stability and speed.\n\n2.  **ECMAIN (Core Engine)**:\n    *   The heart of the local device logic. It includes a script parser (`ECScriptParser`), task polling, and background management systems.\n    *   It handles the execution of custom scripts (including Javascript-based ones found in the root directory).\n\n3.  **Web Control Center**:\n    *   **Backend**: Python-based (FastAPI/Flask likely) managed under `web_control_center/backend`, handling device management and update distribution.\n    *   **Frontend**: A Vue.js application (`web_control_center/frontend`) for visual monitoring and control of connected devices.\n\n4.  **ECHelper (Windows Utilities)**:\n    *   Located in `ECHelper_Windows_Package`, this component provides tools for Windows users to package, build, and deploy the framework to iOS devices.\n\n5.  **Build & Deployment Scripts**:\n    *   Dozens of Python and Ruby scripts (e.g., `add_files_to_xcode.py`, `add_touch_monitor.py`) that automate the complex process of modifying the Xcode project to include custom frameworks and resources like OCR data.\n\n6.  **Advanced Network & System Tools**:\n    *   Integrated components like **Mihomo** (networking/proxy) and **TrollDecrypt** suggest capabilities for handling network traffic and interacting with decrypted application binaries.\n    *   Features like \"De-fingerprinting\" and \"System-level camouflage\" (mentioned in recent commits) point to the project being used to bypass detection in sensitive environments.\n\n7.  **Automation Scripts**:\n    *   Support for localized scripting (e.g., `墨西哥脚本.js`) which allows users to write custom automation logic in JavaScript.\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"mellow-valley","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"Based on the file structure and recent changes, here is an analysis of the project's purpose and key components:\n\n### Main Purpose\nThe project, likely named **\"EC\"** (referencing `ECMAIN` and `ECHelper`), appears to be a **high-performance iOS automation and device management framework**. It is built on a heavily customized version of **WebDriverAgent (WDA)**, designed for low-level device control, screen streaming, and automated script execution. It includes a web-based dashboard and cross-platform (Windows) helper utilities, suggesting it is used for large-scale device clusters (device farms) or complex automation tasks such as mobile game botting or app testing.\n\n### Key Components\n\n1.  **WebDriverAgent (WDA) Customization**:\n    *   Located in `WebDriverAgent.xcodeproj`, `WebDriverAgentLib`, and `WebDriverAgentRunner`.\n    *   Customized with features like OCR engines (`FBOCREngine.mm`), MJPEG server optimizations, and specialized commands (`FBECWDACommands.m`) for stability and speed.\n\n2.  **ECMAIN (Core Engine)**:\n    *   The heart of the local device logic. It includes a script parser (`ECScriptParser`), task polling, and background management systems.\n    *   It handles the execution of custom scripts (including Javascript-based ones found in the root directory).\n\n3.  **Web Control Center**:\n    *   **Backend**: Python-based (FastAPI/Flask likely) managed under `web_control_center/backend`, handling device management and update distribution.\n    *   **Frontend**: A Vue.js application (`web_control_center/frontend`) for visual monitoring and control of connected devices.\n\n4.  **ECHelper (Windows Utilities)**:\n    *   Located in `ECHelper_Windows_Package`, this component provides tools for Windows users to package, build, and deploy the framework to iOS devices.\n\n5.  **Build & Deployment Scripts**:\n    *   Dozens of Python and Ruby scripts (e.g., `add_files_to_xcode.py`, `add_touch_monitor.py`) that automate the complex process of modifying the Xcode project to include custom frameworks and resources like OCR data.\n\n6.  **Advanced Network & System Tools**:\n    *   Integrated components like **Mihomo** (networking/proxy) and **TrollDecrypt** suggest capabilities for handling network traffic and interacting with decrypted application binaries.\n    *   Features like \"De-fingerprinting\" and \"System-level camouflage\" (mentioned in recent commits) point to the project being used to bypass detection in sensitive environments.\n\n7.  **Automation Scripts**:\n    *   Support for localized scripting (e.g., `墨西哥脚本.js`) which allows users to write custom automation logic in JavaScript.\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775205676559}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca4c261a","parentId":"9446737a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:41:20.180Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Discovering Claude Support**\n\nI've made a discovery: `coding-agent` appears to support `claude`, and is available as a skill. I see there's a skill called `coding-agent` and it has the `claude` attribute. Now I'm checking if there's a dedicated `claude` skill.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a99491c327899090","name":"process","arguments":{"limit":100,"action":"log","sessionId":"mellow-valley"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":6898,"output":29,"cacheRead":16225,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23152,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775205676568,"responseId":"chatcmpl-c4b73c68-f5ab-439a-856d-9ea6632a903e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4af0ffd7","parentId":"ca4c261a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:41:20.185Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a99491c327899090","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the file structure and recent changes, here is an analysis of the project's purpose and key components:\n\n### Main Purpose\nThe project, likely named **\"EC\"** (referencing `ECMAIN` and `ECHelper`), appears to be a **high-performance iOS automation and device management framework**. It is built on a heavily customized version of **WebDriverAgent (WDA)**, designed for low-level device control, screen streaming, and automated script execution. It includes a web-based dashboard and cross-platform (Windows) helper utilities, suggesting it is used for large-scale device clusters (device farms) or complex automation tasks such as mobile game botting or app testing.\n\n### Key Components\n\n1.  **WebDriverAgent (WDA) Customization**:\n    *   Located in `WebDriverAgent.xcodeproj`, `WebDriverAgentLib`, and `WebDriverAgentRunner`.\n    *   Customized with features like OCR engines (`FBOCREngine.mm`), MJPEG server optimizations, and specialized commands (`FBECWDACommands.m`) for stability and speed.\n\n2.  **ECMAIN (Core Engine)**:\n    *   The heart of the local device logic. It includes a script parser (`ECScriptParser`), task polling, and background management systems.\n    *   It handles the execution of custom scripts (including Javascript-based ones found in the root directory).\n\n3.  **Web Control Center**:\n    *   **Backend**: Python-based (FastAPI/Flask likely) managed under `web_control_center/backend`, handling device management and update distribution.\n    *   **Frontend**: A Vue.js application (`web_control_center/frontend`) for visual monitoring and control of connected devices.\n\n4.  **ECHelper (Windows Utilities)**:\n    *   Located in `ECHelper_Windows_Package`, this component provides tools for Windows users to package, build, and deploy the framework to iOS devices.\n\n5.  **Build & Deployment Scripts**:\n    *   Dozens of Python and Ruby scripts (e.g., `add_files_to_xcode.py`, `add_touch_monitor.py`) that automate the complex process of modifying the Xcode project to include custom frameworks and resources like OCR data.\n\n6.  **Advanced Network & System Tools**:\n    *   Integrated components like **Mihomo** (networking/proxy) and **TrollDecrypt** suggest capabilities for handling network traffic and interacting with decrypted application binaries.\n    *   Features like \"De-fingerprinting\" and \"System-level camouflage\" (mentioned in recent commits) point to the project being used to bypass detection in sensitive environments.\n\n7.  **Automation Scripts**:\n    *   Support for localized scripting (e.g., `墨西哥脚本.js`) which allows users to write custom automation logic in JavaScript."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"mellow-valley","total":31,"totalLines":31,"totalChars":2624,"truncated":false,"exitCode":0,"name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775205680183}}
{"type":"message","id":"139300e4","parentId":"4af0ffd7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:41:24.423Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"大圣，经过 Claude Code 的分析，`/Users/hh/Desktop/my` 项目（内部代号可能是 **\"EC\"**）是一个**高性能的 iOS 自动化和设备管理框架**。\n\n它的核心功能和组件如下：\n\n1.  **项目定位**：基于高度定制化的 **WebDriverAgent (WDA)**，旨在实现底层设备控制、屏幕串流和自动化脚本执行。它看起来是为大规模设备群（手机墙/设备农场）或者复杂的自动化任务（如手游挂机、App 测试）设计的。\n2.  **核心组件**：\n    *   **定制化 WDA**：在 `WebDriverAgent` 基础上集成了 OCR 引擎（`FBOCREngine`）、MJPEG 串流优化和自定义命令（如 `FBECWDACommands`），大幅提升了稳定性和响应速度。\n    *   **ECMAIN (核心引擎)**：负责设备本地逻辑，包括脚本解析（`ECScriptParser`）、任务轮询和后台管理。\n    *   **Web 控制中心**：包含 Python 后端和 Vue.js 前端，用于可视化监控和管理所有连接的设备。\n    *   **自动化脚本支持**：支持使用 JavaScript 编写自定义脚本（项目中已经能看到如 `墨西哥脚本.js` 之类的示例）。\n3.  **高级特性**：\n    *   集成了 **Mihomo (代理)** 和 **TrollDecrypt (脱壳)**，说明它具备处理网络流量和读取加密 App 的能力。\n    *   具备**反指纹**和**系统级伪装**功能，这通常是为了绕过高强度的风控检测。\n\n简单来说，这是一个非常“硬核”的 iOS 自动化控制系统，涵盖了从底层驱动到上层 Web 管理的全套方案。你需要针对其中的某个模块进行开发吗？🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":7798,"output":399,"cacheRead":16224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24421,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775205680191,"responseId":"chatcmpl-4b637e07-7fc4-4e32-a3de-310a619ce8ee"}}
