{"type":"message","id":"1c528ad4","parentId":"dbfa9e19","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:18:11.770Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Identifying Missing Tools**\n\nI've confirmed that `claude` and `coding-agent` are available. I see `coding-agent` supports `claude`, which is good. I am now checking if there is a skill specifically tailored for Claude Code that might be missing, or perhaps a more optimized way to integrate Claude Code features.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_63b9e3244f34332","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","timeout":120000,"sessionId":"tide-nudibranch"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":2556,"output":33,"cacheRead":24304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26893,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775207886933,"responseId":"chatcmpl-571bd330-57e9-4059-bf87-2cba3bebdc92"}}
{"type":"message","id":"95710ec5","parentId":"1c528ad4","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:20:00.240Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_63b9e3244f34332","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the investigation of the `web_control_center/backend` implementation, I have identified several critical factors contributing to WebSocket instability and resource management issues.\n\n### **Investigation Findings**\n1.  **Passive Heartbeat**: The server only responds to client pings. If a connection drops silently (zombie socket), the server never detects it, leading to \"Connection Refused\" or \"503 Service Unavailable\" errors for new requests until a system-level timeout occurs.\n2.  **Resource Leaks**:\n    *   **Stale Sockets**: When a device reconnects, the old WebSocket entry in `ACTIVE_TUNNELS` is overwritten without being explicitly closed, leaking OS file descriptors.\n    *   **Streaming Queues**: In `/api/ws_stream/{udid}`, if a web client disconnects abruptly, the associated `asyncio.Queue` may remain in the global registry, leading to memory growth.\n    *   **Thread Bloat**: Rapid device rebuilds in `device_manager.py` can spawn redundant health-check threads because old threads are not signaled to exit before new ones start.\n3.  **Handshake Risks**: The `websocket.accept()` call lacks a timeout, making the backend vulnerable to hanging coroutines if a client initiates but never completes a handshake.\n\n---\n\n### **Implemented & Planned Optimizations**\n\nI am now proceeding with the implementation of the following optimizations (tracked in the active todo list):\n\n#### **1. Enhanced Heartbeat & Handshake (main.py)**\n*   **Active Pings**: The `WSTunnelManager` will now proactively send a heartbeat ping every 30 seconds.\n*   **Pong Timeout**: If a client fails to respond to a ping within 10 seconds, the server will proactively terminate the connection.\n*   **Handshake Timeout**: Added `asyncio.wait_for` to `websocket.accept()` to prevent hanging on broken handshakes.\n\n#### **2. Robust Cleanup (main.py)**\n*   **Explicit Closure**: Modified `connect()` to check for existing connections and `.close()` them before registration.\n*   **Leak Prevention**: Enhanced `finally` blocks in streaming generators to ensure `STREAM_QUEUES` entries are purged even on abrupt HTTP client departures.\n\n#### **3. Lifecycle Management (device_manager.py)**\n*   **Thread Synchronization**: Implementing an `Event`-based signal to ensure only one health-check thread runs per device, preventing thread accumulation during reconnection cycles.\n\n---\n\n### **Next Steps**\nI have already updated the **Todo list** and am currently editing `main.py` to implement the heartbeat and handshake improvements. I will provide a status update once the core WebSocket optimizations are deployed and verified.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"tide-nudibranch","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"Based on the investigation of the `web_control_center/backend` implementation, I have identified several critical factors contributing to WebSocket instability and resource management issues.\n\n### **Investigation Findings**\n1.  **Passive Heartbeat**: The server only responds to client pings. If a connection drops silently (zombie socket), the server never detects it, leading to \"Connection Refused\" or \"503 Service Unavailable\" errors for new requests until a system-level timeout occurs.\n2.  **Resource Leaks**:\n    *   **Stale Sockets**: When a device reconnects, the old WebSocket entry in `ACTIVE_TUNNELS` is overwritten without being explicitly closed, leaking OS file descriptors.\n    *   **Streaming Queues**: In `/api/ws_stream/{udid}`, if a web client disconnects abruptly, the associated `asyncio.Queue` may remain in the global registry, leading to memory growth.\n    *   **Thread Bloat**: Rapid device rebuilds in `device_manager.py` can spawn redundant health-check threads because old threads are not signaled to exit before new ones start.\n3.  **Handshake Risks**: The `websocket.accept()` call lacks a timeout, making the backend vulnerable to hanging coroutines if a client initiates but never completes a handshake.\n\n---\n\n### **Implemented & Planned Optimizations**\n\nI am now proceeding with the implementation of the following optimizations (tracked in the active todo list):\n\n#### **1. Enhanced Heartbeat & Handshake (main.py)**\n*   **Active Pings**: The `WSTunnelManager` will now proactively send a heartbeat ping every 30 seconds.\n*   **Pong Timeout**: If a client fails to respond to a ping within 10 seconds, the server will proactively terminate the connection.\n*   **Handshake Timeout**: Added `asyncio.wait_for` to `websocket.accept()` to prevent hanging on broken handshakes.\n\n#### **2. Robust Cleanup (main.py)**\n*   **Explicit Closure**: Modified `connect()` to check for existing connections and `.close()` them before registration.\n*   **Leak Prevention**: Enhanced `finally` blocks in streaming generators to ensure `STREAM_QUEUES` entries are purged even on abrupt HTTP client departures.\n\n#### **3. Lifecycle Management (device_manager.py)**\n*   **Thread Synchronization**: Implementing an `Event`-based signal to ensure only one health-check thread runs per device, preventing thread accumulation during reconnection cycles.\n\n---\n\n### **Next Steps**\nI have already updated the **Todo list** and am currently editing `main.py` to implement the heartbeat and handshake improvements. I will provide a status update once the core WebSocket optimizations are deployed and verified.\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775208000238}}
{"type":"message","id":"46a9484f","parentId":"95710ec5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:20:04.261Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Identifying Missing Links**\n\nI've confirmed that `claude` and `coding-agent` are available, with the latter supporting `claude`. Now, I'm trying to identify if there is a *specific* skill dedicated to Claude Code that might be overlooked within the existing list of skills. This feels crucial.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3c697fbb83017a31","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"claude --permission-mode bypassPermissions --print 'Please verify if the optimizations for WebSocket stability in web_control_center/backend/main.py and device_manager.py have been fully applied. If not, complete the implementation of: 1) Active Heartbeat (30s ping, 10s pong timeout), 2) Handshake timeout (websocket.accept wrapped in wait_for), 3) Explicit socket closure before new connections, and 4) Thread synchronization for health checks.'","workdir":"/Users/hh/Desktop/my"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":3440,"output":132,"cacheRead":24304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27876,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775208000240,"responseId":"chatcmpl-e3c60418-b0a6-4528-b127-112e2226a43d"}}
