{"type":"message","id":"d4827d74","parentId":"047e99c4","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:22:12.105Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_fbc26ae147157125","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have verified the implementation in `ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.m` and confirmed that the planned exponential backoff for WebSocket reconnection has **not** been applied. The current implementation uses a fixed 60-second delay for all reconnection attempts.\n\nI have created a comprehensive implementation plan to address this:\n\n### 📋 Implementation Plan: Exponential Backoff for WebSocket Reconnection\n\n#### 1. Add `_reconnectAttemptCount` ivar\n*   Update the `@implementation ECBackgroundManager` block in `ECBackgroundManager.m:56-71` to include `NSInteger _reconnectAttemptCount;`.\n\n#### 2. Reset count on successful connection\n*   In `URLSession:webSocketTask:didOpenWithProtocol:` (around line 935), reset `_reconnectAttemptCount = 0;` once the connection is confirmed.\n\n#### 3. Add `_scheduleExponentialReconnect` method\n*   Implement a new private method that calculates the delay based on `_reconnectAttemptCount` (1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s, capped at 30s) and calls the existing `_scheduleReconnectWithDelay:`.\n\n#### 4. Update all reconnection call sites\n*   Replace the fixed 60s reconnection intervals with calls to `_scheduleExponentialReconnect` in:\n    *   **`startTunnel`**: Error during URL escaping (line 898).\n    *   **`URLSession:webSocketTask:didCloseWithCode:reason:`**: Connection closed (line 974).\n    *   **`URLSession:task:didCompleteWithError:`**: Session errors (line 1009).\n    *   **`receiveTunnelMessage`**: Message handling errors (line 1057).\n\n### 🔍 Verification Strategy\n*   Monitor console logs for `[Tunnel]` entries.\n*   Simulate failures to verify that the delay intervals correctly double until reaching the 30s cap.\n*   Confirm that a successful connection successfully resets the backoff counter.\n\nThe full plan is available in `/Users/hh/.claude/plans/curried-tickling-pnueli.md`. Please review and approve to proceed with the implementation.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"wild-cove","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"I have verified the implementation in `ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.m` and confirmed that the planned exponential backoff for WebSocket reconnection has **not** been applied. The current implementation uses a fixed 60-second delay for all reconnection attempts.\n\nI have created a comprehensive implementation plan to address this:\n\n### 📋 Implementation Plan: Exponential Backoff for WebSocket Reconnection\n\n#### 1. Add `_reconnectAttemptCount` ivar\n*   Update the `@implementation ECBackgroundManager` block in `ECBackgroundManager.m:56-71` to include `NSInteger _reconnectAttemptCount;`.\n\n#### 2. Reset count on successful connection\n*   In `URLSession:webSocketTask:didOpenWithProtocol:` (around line 935), reset `_reconnectAttemptCount = 0;` once the connection is confirmed.\n\n#### 3. Add `_scheduleExponentialReconnect` method\n*   Implement a new private method that calculates the delay based on `_reconnectAttemptCount` (1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s, capped at 30s) and calls the existing `_scheduleReconnectWithDelay:`.\n\n#### 4. Update all reconnection call sites\n*   Replace the fixed 60s reconnection intervals with calls to `_scheduleExponentialReconnect` in:\n    *   **`startTunnel`**: Error during URL escaping (line 898).\n    *   **`URLSession:webSocketTask:didCloseWithCode:reason:`**: Connection closed (line 974).\n    *   **`URLSession:task:didCompleteWithError:`**: Session errors (line 1009).\n    *   **`receiveTunnelMessage`**: Message handling errors (line 1057).\n\n### 🔍 Verification Strategy\n*   Monitor console logs for `[Tunnel]` entries.\n*   Simulate failures to verify that the delay intervals correctly double until reaching the 30s cap.\n*   Confirm that a successful connection successfully resets the backoff counter.\n\nThe full plan is available in `/Users/hh/.claude/plans/curried-tickling-pnueli.md`. Please review and approve to proceed with the implementation.\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775208132104}}
