{"type":"message","id":"81dc3b9f","parentId":"591504e1","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:22:43.451Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_88fe675d767bd8cf","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have prepared the implementation plan for the exponential backoff for WebSocket reconnection in `ECBackgroundManager.m`.\n\n### Updated `ECBackgroundManager.m` Implementation Plan\n\n#### 1. Added `_reconnectAttemptCount` Ivar\nLocated in the `@implementation ECBackgroundManager` extension block (around line 71):\n```objectivec\n@implementation ECBackgroundManager {\n  // ... existing ivars\n  NSInteger _reconnectAttemptCount; // Added for backoff\n}\n```\n\n#### 2. Reset Count on Successful Connection\nUpdated `URLSession:webSocketTask:didOpenWithProtocol:` (around line 935):\n```objectivec\n- (void)URLSession:(NSURLSession *)session\n          webSocketTask:(NSURLSessionWebSocketTask *)webSocketTask\n    didOpenWithProtocol:(NSString *)protocol {\n  @synchronized(self) {\n    if (self->_webSocketTask != webSocketTask) return;\n    self->_isTunnelConnected = YES;\n    self->_isTunnelConnecting = NO;\n    self->_reconnectAttemptCount = 0; // Reset counter\n  }\n  // ...\n}\n```\n\n#### 3. New Exponential Reconnect Method\nAdded after `_scheduleReconnectWithDelay:` (around line 820):\n```objectivec\n- (void)_scheduleExponentialReconnect {\n    _reconnectAttemptCount++;\n    double delay = pow(2.0, (double)(_reconnectAttemptCount - 1));\n    if (delay > 30.0) delay = 30.0;\n    [self _scheduleReconnectWithDelay:delay];\n}\n```\n\n#### 4. Updated Reconnection Call Sites (4 locations)\nReplacing `[self _scheduleReconnectWithDelay:60.0]` or similar:\n- **`startTunnel`**: For URL escaping errors (line 898) and invalid URL (line 909).\n- **`didCloseWithCode`**: After disconnect (line 974).\n- **`didCompleteWithError`**: Session-level errors (line 1009).\n- **`receiveTunnelMessage`**: Message loop errors (line 1057).\n\nThe backoff sequence will be **1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s, 30s (capped)**, significantly improving responsiveness while protecting the server during outages.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"marine-harbor","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"I have prepared the implementation plan for the exponential backoff for WebSocket reconnection in `ECBackgroundManager.m`.\n\n### Updated `ECBackgroundManager.m` Implementation Plan\n\n#### 1. Added `_reconnectAttemptCount` Ivar\nLocated in the `@implementation ECBackgroundManager` extension block (around line 71):\n```objectivec\n@implementation ECBackgroundManager {\n  // ... existing ivars\n  NSInteger _reconnectAttemptCount; // Added for backoff\n}\n```\n\n#### 2. Reset Count on Successful Connection\nUpdated `URLSession:webSocketTask:didOpenWithProtocol:` (around line 935):\n```objectivec\n- (void)URLSession:(NSURLSession *)session\n          webSocketTask:(NSURLSessionWebSocketTask *)webSocketTask\n    didOpenWithProtocol:(NSString *)protocol {\n  @synchronized(self) {\n    if (self->_webSocketTask != webSocketTask) return;\n    self->_isTunnelConnected = YES;\n    self->_isTunnelConnecting = NO;\n    self->_reconnectAttemptCount = 0; // Reset counter\n  }\n  // ...\n}\n```\n\n#### 3. New Exponential Reconnect Method\nAdded after `_scheduleReconnectWithDelay:` (around line 820):\n```objectivec\n- (void)_scheduleExponentialReconnect {\n    _reconnectAttemptCount++;\n    double delay = pow(2.0, (double)(_reconnectAttemptCount - 1));\n    if (delay > 30.0) delay = 30.0;\n    [self _scheduleReconnectWithDelay:delay];\n}\n```\n\n#### 4. Updated Reconnection Call Sites (4 locations)\nReplacing `[self _scheduleReconnectWithDelay:60.0]` or similar:\n- **`startTunnel`**: For URL escaping errors (line 898) and invalid URL (line 909).\n- **`didCloseWithCode`**: After disconnect (line 974).\n- **`didCompleteWithError`**: Session-level errors (line 1009).\n- **`receiveTunnelMessage`**: Message loop errors (line 1057).\n\nThe backoff sequence will be **1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s, 30s (capped)**, significantly improving responsiveness while protecting the server during outages.\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775208163449}}
