{"type":"message","id":"cf949052","parentId":"d7fe567b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:41:02.957Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ffa7c44ad8e02be3","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have implemented the reciprocal health check in **ECWDA** to monitor **ECMAIN**. This ensures that if ECMAIN becomes unresponsive, ECWDA will attempt to recover it.\n\n### Summary of Changes\n\n#### 1. Implemented Reciprocal Health Check in `XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m`\nAdded a background monitor that pings ECMAIN at `http://127.0.0.1:8089/ping` every **30 seconds**.\n*   **Threshold**: If pings fail for **3 consecutive checks**, a relaunch is triggered.\n*   **Recovery**: Uses `FBUnattachedAppLauncher` to relaunch `com.ecmain.app` in the background (supporting locked-screen scenarios).\n*   **Safety**: Implemented a **60-second cooldown** to prevent infinite restart loops.\n*   **Initialization**: The monitoring starts 10 seconds after WDA launch to allow the network stack and system services to stabilize.\n\n#### 2. Cleaned up `FBECWDACommands.m`\n*   Removed the legacy 60-second keep-alive timer and its associated `checkEcmainAlive` logic.\n*   Centralized all health monitoring logic within the `XCUIDevice` category to avoid redundant network traffic and conflicting state updates on port 8089.\n\n### Files Modified:\n- `WebDriverAgentLib/Categories/XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m`\n- `WebDriverAgentLib/Commands/FBECWDACommands.m`\n\nThe system now has a two-way watchdog: ECMAIN monitors WDA's liveness, and ECWDA now actively monitors and revives ECMAIN via its internal HTTP server.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"dawn-basil","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"I have implemented the reciprocal health check in **ECWDA** to monitor **ECMAIN**. This ensures that if ECMAIN becomes unresponsive, ECWDA will attempt to recover it.\n\n### Summary of Changes\n\n#### 1. Implemented Reciprocal Health Check in `XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m`\nAdded a background monitor that pings ECMAIN at `http://127.0.0.1:8089/ping` every **30 seconds**.\n*   **Threshold**: If pings fail for **3 consecutive checks**, a relaunch is triggered.\n*   **Recovery**: Uses `FBUnattachedAppLauncher` to relaunch `com.ecmain.app` in the background (supporting locked-screen scenarios).\n*   **Safety**: Implemented a **60-second cooldown** to prevent infinite restart loops.\n*   **Initialization**: The monitoring starts 10 seconds after WDA launch to allow the network stack and system services to stabilize.\n\n#### 2. Cleaned up `FBECWDACommands.m`\n*   Removed the legacy 60-second keep-alive timer and its associated `checkEcmainAlive` logic.\n*   Centralized all health monitoring logic within the `XCUIDevice` category to avoid redundant network traffic and conflicting state updates on port 8089.\n\n### Files Modified:\n- `WebDriverAgentLib/Categories/XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m`\n- `WebDriverAgentLib/Commands/FBECWDACommands.m`\n\nThe system now has a two-way watchdog: ECMAIN monitors WDA's liveness, and ECWDA now actively monitors and revives ECMAIN via its internal HTTP server.\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775209262954}}
{"type":"message","id":"1482fd7e","parentId":"cf949052","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:41:07.603Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Identifying Missing Skills**\n\nI've confirmed that `claude` and `coding-agent` are available. I reviewed the `available_skills` and confirmed `coding-agent` supports `claude-code`. I'm now focusing on whether a specific skill tailored to Claude Code might be missing, and am investigating its absence.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4fac8e7f3ee50f0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"claude --permission-mode bypassPermissions --print 'Please verify the implementation of the reciprocal health check in XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m and FBECWDACommands.m. Ensure: 1) The ping to 127.0.0.1:8089 is correctly implemented with a 10s timeout, 2) 3 consecutive failures trigger the relaunch, 3) The relaunch uses com.ecmain.app and FBUnattachedAppLauncher, and 4) The 60-second cooldown is enforced to prevent infinite restart loops. Report any missing pieces or edge cases like Wi-Fi/Network stack delays during boot.'","workdir":"/Users/hh/Desktop/my"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":2824,"output":167,"cacheRead":56814,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59805,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775209262958,"responseId":"chatcmpl-9c5a3ce9-e164-4499-ab57-2cc7c4d90efc"}}
