{"type":"message","id":"b78dfc9b","parentId":"8fd39865","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:41:24.261Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_268e80274374effb","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my verification of the codebase, here is the implementation report for the reciprocal health check between **ECWDA** and **ECMAIN**:\n\n### 1. Verification of Requirements\n\n| Requirement | Status | Implementation Details |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Ping 127.0.0.1:8089** | ✅ **Partial** | Implemented in `XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m:34`. However, it uses a **5s timeout**, not the requested **10s** (`request.timeoutInterval = 5.0;`). |\n| **3 Consecutive Failures** | ✅ **Passed** | Implemented via `static NSInteger _ecmainFailureCount`. It triggers relaunch when count `>= 3` and resets on success (`XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m:45, 52`). |\n| **Relaunch Mechanism** | ✅ **Passed** | Correctly uses `com.ecmain.app` and `FBUnattachedAppLauncher` to launch in the background (`XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m:70`). |\n| **60s Cooldown** | ✅ **Passed** | Enforced using `_lastEcmainLaunchTime`. Relaunch is skipped if `now - last < 60.0` (`XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m:60`). |\n\n### 2. Implementation Overview\n\n**`XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m`**\n*   **Initialization:** The health check starts automatically via `+load`. It includes a **10-second initial delay** to allow the network stack and ECMAIN to initialize after boot.\n*   **Polling Interval:** The check runs every **30 seconds**.\n*   **Logic Consolidation:** As noted in `FBECWDACommands.m:54`, the health check logic was successfully migrated from the commands file to this category for cleaner lifecycle management.\n\n### 3. Missing Pieces & Edge Cases\n\n*   **Timeout Mismatch:** As noted above, the code currently enforces a `5.0s` timeout for the HTTP request. If the network stack is heavily congested or the device is under extreme load (common during boot), 5 seconds might be too aggressive, leading to false-positive failure increments.\n*   **Initial Boot Delay:** The `dispatch_after` wait of 10 seconds in `+load` is a good start, but in real-world \"cold boot\" scenarios, Wi-Fi connectivity and local network stack availability can often take 20–30 seconds. \n*   **Race Conditions:** The failure counter is a static variable manipulated inside an asynchronous `NSURLSession` completion block. While the 30s interval makes collisions unlikely, it is not explicitly thread-safe.\n*   **Hardcoded Endpoint:** The ping endpoint `http://127.0.0.1:8089/ping` is hardcoded. If ECMAIN's configuration changes, WDA will enter a restart loop (throttled by the 60s cooldown).\n\n### Recommendation\nUpdate the `timeoutInterval` in `XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m:37` from `5.0` to `10.0` to align with your requirement and improve stability during high-load boot sequences.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"dawn-otter","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"Based on my verification of the codebase, here is the implementation report for the reciprocal health check between **ECWDA** and **ECMAIN**:\n\n### 1. Verification of Requirements\n\n| Requirement | Status | Implementation Details |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Ping 127.0.0.1:8089** | ✅ **Partial** | Implemented in `XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m:34`. However, it uses a **5s timeout**, not the requested **10s** (`request.timeoutInterval = 5.0;`). |\n| **3 Consecutive Failures** | ✅ **Passed** | Implemented via `static NSInteger _ecmainFailureCount`. It triggers relaunch when count `>= 3` and resets on success (`XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m:45, 52`). |\n| **Relaunch Mechanism** | ✅ **Passed** | Correctly uses `com.ecmain.app` and `FBUnattachedAppLauncher` to launch in the background (`XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m:70`). |\n| **60s Cooldown** | ✅ **Passed** | Enforced using `_lastEcmainLaunchTime`. Relaunch is skipped if `now - last < 60.0` (`XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m:60`). |\n\n### 2. Implementation Overview\n\n**`XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m`**\n*   **Initialization:** The health check starts automatically via `+load`. It includes a **10-second initial delay** to allow the network stack and ECMAIN to initialize after boot.\n*   **Polling Interval:** The check runs every **30 seconds**.\n*   **Logic Consolidation:** As noted in `FBECWDACommands.m:54`, the health check logic was successfully migrated from the commands file to this category for cleaner lifecycle management.\n\n### 3. Missing Pieces & Edge Cases\n\n*   **Timeout Mismatch:** As noted above, the code currently enforces a `5.0s` timeout for the HTTP request. If the network stack is heavily congested or the device is under extreme load (common during boot), 5 seconds might be too aggressive, leading to false-positive failure increments.\n*   **Initial Boot Delay:** The `dispatch_after` wait of 10 seconds in `+load` is a good start, but in real-world \"cold boot\" scenarios, Wi-Fi connectivity and local network stack availability can often take 20–30 seconds. \n*   **Race Conditions:** The failure counter is a static variable manipulated inside an asynchronous `NSURLSession` completion block. While the 30s interval makes collisions unlikely, it is not explicitly thread-safe.\n*   **Hardcoded Endpoint:** The ping endpoint `http://127.0.0.1:8089/ping` is hardcoded. If ECMAIN's configuration changes, WDA will enter a restart loop (throttled by the 60s cooldown).\n\n### Recommendation\nUpdate the `timeoutInterval` in `XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m:37` from `5.0` to `10.0` to align with your requirement and improve stability during high-load boot sequences.\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775209284259}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a808406","parentId":"b78dfc9b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:41:28.727Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Identifying Missing Skills**\n\nOkay, I've confirmed `claude` is installed. I've re-examined `available_skills` and confirmed the presence of `coding-agent`. Interestingly, this agent supports `claude-code`. I'm now trying to determine if there's a specific skill dedicated to `claude-code` that I might have overlooked. Is there something explicitly for this sub-tool that's absent?\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d71481bfb2830bcc","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"claude --permission-mode bypassPermissions --print 'The implementation is good but let us refine it: 1) Increase timeoutInterval to 10.0 in XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m (line 37), 2) Increase initial delay in +load to 30.0s to allow for real-world cold boot network stack stabilization, and 3) Make the failure counter thread-safe using @synchronized or atomic operations.'","workdir":"/Users/hh/Desktop/my"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":4299,"output":122,"cacheRead":56808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61229,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775209284262,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1e4d8249-2303-4d95-bb86-a627dd971bad"}}
