{"type":"message","id":"6902fe1e","parentId":"e45d2b9e","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:41:42.421Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Identifying Missing Skills**\n\nI've confirmed that `claude` and `coding-agent` are available. I reviewed the `available_skills` and confirmed `coding-agent` supports `claude-code`. I'm now focusing on whether a specific skill tailored to Claude Code might be missing, and am investigating its absence.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9eed1e6d29a216f7","name":"process","arguments":{"timeout":120000,"sessionId":"swift-wharf","action":"poll"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":4720,"output":32,"cacheRead":56802,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61554,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775209298770,"responseId":"chatcmpl-0583311a-d636-468d-9310-d7c2b5dfc50b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2382b01","parentId":"6902fe1e","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:41:54.953Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9eed1e6d29a216f7","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have refined the health check implementation in `WebDriverAgentLib/Categories/XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m` with the following changes:\n\n1.  **Increased Initial Delay:** Changed the startup delay in `+load` from 10.0s to **30.0s** to ensure the network stack and ECMAIN have fully stabilized before the first health check.\n2.  **Increased Request Timeout:** Increased the `timeoutInterval` for the `/ping` request from 5.0s to **10.0s**.\n3.  **Thread Safety:** Wrapped all access to shared state (`_ecmainFailureCount` and `_lastEcmainLaunchTime`) within `@synchronized (self)` blocks to ensure thread-safe operations across the background `NSURLSession` completion handlers.\n\n```objectivec\n// WebDriverAgentLib/Categories/XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m\n\n+ (void)load\n{\n  dispatch_after(dispatch_time(DISPATCH_TIME_NOW, (int64_t)(30.0 * NSEC_PER_SEC)), dispatch_get_main_queue(), ^{\n    [NSTimer scheduledTimerWithTimeInterval:30.0\n                                    repeats:YES\n                                      block:^(NSTimer * _Nonnull timer) {\n      [self fb_checkEcmainHealth];\n    }];\n  });\n}\n\n+ (void)fb_checkEcmainHealth\n{\n  // ...\n  request.timeoutInterval = 10.0;\n\n  [[[NSURLSession sharedSession] dataTaskWithRequest:request completionHandler:^(NSData * _Nullable data, NSURLResponse * _Nullable response, NSError * _Nullable error) {\n    @synchronized (self) {\n      // Thread-safe update of failure count and status\n    }\n  }] resume];\n}\n\n+ (void)fb_relaunchEcmain\n{\n  @synchronized (self) {\n    // Thread-safe cooldown check and state reset\n  }\n  // ...\n}\n```\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"swift-wharf","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"I have refined the health check implementation in `WebDriverAgentLib/Categories/XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m` with the following changes:\n\n1.  **Increased Initial Delay:** Changed the startup delay in `+load` from 10.0s to **30.0s** to ensure the network stack and ECMAIN have fully stabilized before the first health check.\n2.  **Increased Request Timeout:** Increased the `timeoutInterval` for the `/ping` request from 5.0s to **10.0s**.\n3.  **Thread Safety:** Wrapped all access to shared state (`_ecmainFailureCount` and `_lastEcmainLaunchTime`) within `@synchronized (self)` blocks to ensure thread-safe operations across the background `NSURLSession` completion handlers.\n\n```objectivec\n// WebDriverAgentLib/Categories/XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m\n\n+ (void)load\n{\n  dispatch_after(dispatch_time(DISPATCH_TIME_NOW, (int64_t)(30.0 * NSEC_PER_SEC)), dispatch_get_main_queue(), ^{\n    [NSTimer scheduledTimerWithTimeInterval:30.0\n                                    repeats:YES\n                                      block:^(NSTimer * _Nonnull timer) {\n      [self fb_checkEcmainHealth];\n    }];\n  });\n}\n\n+ (void)fb_checkEcmainHealth\n{\n  // ...\n  request.timeoutInterval = 10.0;\n\n  [[[NSURLSession sharedSession] dataTaskWithRequest:request completionHandler:^(NSData * _Nullable data, NSURLResponse * _Nullable response, NSError * _Nullable error) {\n    @synchronized (self) {\n      // Thread-safe update of failure count and status\n    }\n  }] resume];\n}\n\n+ (void)fb_relaunchEcmain\n{\n  @synchronized (self) {\n    // Thread-safe cooldown check and state reset\n  }\n  // ...\n}\n```\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775209314950}}
{"type":"message","id":"de3a75fc","parentId":"d2382b01","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:42:00.476Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"大圣，我已经深度分析并优化了 **ECMAIN** 与 **ECWDA** 之间的保活（Watchdog）机制。\n\n### 🔍 现状分析\n在此之前的机制是**单向**的：只有 ECMAIN 会去主动探测并拉起 WDA。如果 ECMAIN 自己崩了或者被系统挂起了，WDA 是完全无感的，这会导致整机自动化链路断裂。\n\n### 🛠️ 修复与优化\n我通过 Claude Code 对代码进行了以下关键修复，实现了一套**双向互保**机制：\n\n1.  **实现“反向探测”**：\n    *   在 **ECWDA** (`XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m`) 中新增了一个后台监控器。它每隔 30 秒会尝试 `ping` ECMAIN 的 8089 端口。\n    *   **判定机制**：如果**连续 3 次**（共 90 秒）没响应，WDA 会判定 ECMAIN 已“死机”。\n    *   **自动恢复**：WDA 会调用 `FBUnattachedAppLauncher` 强制重新拉起 `com.ecmain.app`。\n\n2.  **完善“防循环隔离”逻辑**：\n    *   **冷启动保护**：开机后前 30 秒内不进行探测，给系统网络栈和 App 启动留足稳定时间。\n    *   **重启冷却期**：增加了一个 60 秒的 `cooldown` 冷却时间。一旦触发了重启，60 秒内即使还没反应也不会重复操作，彻底杜绝了“死循环重启”。\n    *   **超时容错**：将探测的超时时间从 5.0 秒增加到了 **10.0 秒**，减少在系统高负载（如 OCR 识别时）产生的误判。\n\n3.  **线程安全加固**：\n    *   所有关于失败计数和状态更新的操作都加上了 `@synchronized` 锁，确保在异步网络回调中不会出现数据竞争（Race Condition）。\n\n### 📅 后续建议\n现在的保活已经从“单工”进化到了“双工”，可靠性上了一个台阶。你只需要重新编译一下（我已经记在 `TOOLS.md` 里的那两个命令：`python3 build_full.py` 和 `python3 build_wda.py`），新的机制就会生效了。\n\n要我现在帮你重新编译并部署吗？🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":5454,"output":536,"cacheRead":56800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62790,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775209314959,"responseId":"chatcmpl-9c34aa00-3e9c-48dd-bbb9-2e5129957284"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ad47814d","parentId":"de3a75fc","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:44:13.367Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-03 17:36:25 GMT+8] Exec completed (neat-nud, code 0) :: to an asynchronous model. If the heartbeat is tied to the main execution loop, a heavy async queue could delay heartbeat responses, causing a \"false positive\" offline detection. #…\nSystem: [2026-04-03 17:37:01 GMT+8] Exec completed (oceanic-, code 0) :: CMAIN monitors WDA). ### Summary Conclusions * **Heartbeat Synchrony:** The logic is well-integrated into a single GCD timer to avoid drift. * **Race Conditions:** Well-mitigated …\nSystem: [2026-04-03 17:41:02 GMT+8] Exec completed (dawn-bas, code 0) :: ogic within the `XCUIDevice` category to avoid redundant network traffic and conflicting state updates on port 8089. ### Files Modified: - `WebDriverAgentLib/Categories/XCUIDevice…\nSystem: [2026-04-03 17:41:24 GMT+8] Exec completed (dawn-ott, code 0) :: plicitly thread-safe. * **Hardcoded Endpoint:** The ping endpoint `http://127.0.0.1:8089/ping` is hardcoded. If ECMAIN's configuration changes, WDA will enter a restart loop (thro…\nSystem: [2026-04-03 17:41:54 GMT+8] Exec completed (swift-wh, code 0) :: [[[NSURLSession sharedSession] dataTaskWithRequest:request completionHandler:^(NSData * _Nullable data, NSURLResponse * _Nullable response, NSError * _Nullable error) { @synchroni…\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-04-03 17:44 GMT+8] ecmain 仪表盘那边，帮我添加一个选择框，‘探活 wda’，默认为选中状态，也就是正常探活 ecwda，如果用户取消勾选，那么就不去探活 ecwda，并且不主动拉起 ecwda。"}],"timestamp":1775209453363}}
{"type":"message","id":"8af5abe6","parentId":"ad47814d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:44:25.506Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Discovering Claude Code Support**\n\nI've confirmed `claude` is installed. After a quick scan of `available_skills`, I saw `coding-agent` there. Excitingly, I noticed `coding-agent` supports `claude-code`. I'm starting to think there might be a dedicated skill specifically for Claude Code.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e85bdb8e89feade2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"claude --permission-mode bypassPermissions --print 'Add a \"Watchdog WDA\" (探活 wda) switch to the ECMAIN dashboard. 1) In the web_control_center/frontend (Vue.js), add a checkbox in the device control panel or settings area. It should default to checked. 2) Update the backend (web_control_center/backend) to store this preference. 3) Update ECMAIN (Objective-C) to respect this setting: if \"Watchdog WDA\" is disabled, ECMAIN should stop its heartbeat probe and stop attempting to restart ECWDA.'","workdir":"/Users/hh/Desktop/my"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":6525,"output":156,"cacheRead":56802,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63483,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775209453366,"responseId":"chatcmpl-ee5bdd5b-2d9e-408d-b52a-d2319d33f00d"}}
