{"type":"message","id":"fcb1c950","parentId":"2cc3e2a7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:46:56.225Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Discovering Claude Code Support**\n\nI've confirmed `claude` is installed. After a quick scan of `available_skills`, I saw `coding-agent`. Interestingly, this `coding-agent` skill supports `claude-code`. That's a great find.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4141af61ce696b1c","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","timeout":240000,"sessionId":"rapid-fjord"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":7280,"output":31,"cacheRead":56790,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64101,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775209610249,"responseId":"chatcmpl-0f4a35ab-88b8-4845-b06e-f8837622c98a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"abd5d0e0","parentId":"fcb1c950","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:48:49.786Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4141af61ce696b1c","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have completed the implementation of the \"Watchdog WDA\" (探活 wda) switch. Here is the summary of the changes:\n\n### 1. Backend Updates (Python)\n- **Database (`database.py`):** Added a `watchdog_wda` column (INTEGER, default 1) to the `ec_devices` table. Updated `get_device_config` and `set_device_config` to handle this new field.\n- **Heartbeat & API (`main.py`):** \n    - Updated `DeviceConfigRequest` Pydantic model.\n    - Updated the configuration sync logic: `watchdog_wda` is now part of the `config_checksum` (MD5).\n    - When a config mismatch is detected, the backend pushes the `watchdog_wda` value to the device in the `push_config` dictionary.\n\n### 2. Frontend Updates (Vue.js)\n- **UI (`App.vue`):** Added a checkbox labeled **\"Watchdog WDA\" (探活 wda)** in the Device Settings modal/panel.\n- **State management:** The checkbox defaults to `true` (checked) for new configurations and respects the saved value from the database for existing devices.\n\n### 3. ECMAIN Updates (Objective-C)\n- **Settings Persistence:** ECMAIN now extracts `watchdog_wda` from the heartbeat's `push_config` and persists it to `NSUserDefaults` (key: `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED`).\n- **Watchdog Logic (`ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m`):** Added a conditional check in the heartbeat loop. If `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED` is set to `NO`, ECMAIN skips the `/status` probe to `127.0.0.1:10088` and refrains from attempting to restart `ECWDA`.\n\nThe feature is now fully integrated across the stack, allowing users to selectively disable the WDA watchdog for specific devices directly from the control panel.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"rapid-fjord","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"I have completed the implementation of the \"Watchdog WDA\" (探活 wda) switch. Here is the summary of the changes:\n\n### 1. Backend Updates (Python)\n- **Database (`database.py`):** Added a `watchdog_wda` column (INTEGER, default 1) to the `ec_devices` table. Updated `get_device_config` and `set_device_config` to handle this new field.\n- **Heartbeat & API (`main.py`):** \n    - Updated `DeviceConfigRequest` Pydantic model.\n    - Updated the configuration sync logic: `watchdog_wda` is now part of the `config_checksum` (MD5).\n    - When a config mismatch is detected, the backend pushes the `watchdog_wda` value to the device in the `push_config` dictionary.\n\n### 2. Frontend Updates (Vue.js)\n- **UI (`App.vue`):** Added a checkbox labeled **\"Watchdog WDA\" (探活 wda)** in the Device Settings modal/panel.\n- **State management:** The checkbox defaults to `true` (checked) for new configurations and respects the saved value from the database for existing devices.\n\n### 3. ECMAIN Updates (Objective-C)\n- **Settings Persistence:** ECMAIN now extracts `watchdog_wda` from the heartbeat's `push_config` and persists it to `NSUserDefaults` (key: `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED`).\n- **Watchdog Logic (`ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m`):** Added a conditional check in the heartbeat loop. If `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED` is set to `NO`, ECMAIN skips the `/status` probe to `127.0.0.1:10088` and refrains from attempting to restart `ECWDA`.\n\nThe feature is now fully integrated across the stack, allowing users to selectively disable the WDA watchdog for specific devices directly from the control panel.\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775209729784}}
