{"type":"message","id":"31bd56c9","parentId":"209ea424","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:50:01.720Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d9a93624dfebba5d","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I've implemented the **Watchdog WDA** (探活 WDA) switch across the frontend and the ECMAIN client.\n\n### 1. Frontend Implementation\nUpdated `web_control_center/frontend/src/App.vue` to include the toggle in the device settings modal.\n- Added a checkbox labeled **\"探活 wda\"**.\n- Linked it to the device settings model with a default value of `true`.\n- Ensured it persists when settings are saved.\n\n### 2. ECMAIN Client Implementation\nUpdated the backend logic in the ECMAIN client to honor the new setting.\n\n**ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.h & .m:**\n- Added a `watchdogWDA` property to `ECBackgroundManager`.\n- Implemented persistence using `NSUserDefaults` under the key `\"EC_WATCHDOG_WDA\"`.\n- Added a public getter/setter to allow the UI or heartbeat to toggle the setting.\n\n**ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m:**\n- Modified the `sendHeartbeat:` method to check the `watchdogWDA` setting.\n- The WDA health check (probing port `10089` and `10088`) is now **skipped** if the setting is `false`.\n- This prevents the watchdog from forcefully restarting WDA when the user intentionally disables the probe.\n\n### Summary of Changes:\n- **Frontend**: Added UI checkbox for \"Watchdog WDA\".\n- **Client Core**: Added local storage for the watchdog preference.\n- **Heartbeat Logic**: Integrated the preference to conditionally skip health checks and auto-restarts of the WDA process.\n\nThe \"Watchdog WDA\" switch is now fully functional from the web control panel down to the device-level heartbeat logic.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"calm-canyon","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"I've implemented the **Watchdog WDA** (探活 WDA) switch across the frontend and the ECMAIN client.\n\n### 1. Frontend Implementation\nUpdated `web_control_center/frontend/src/App.vue` to include the toggle in the device settings modal.\n- Added a checkbox labeled **\"探活 wda\"**.\n- Linked it to the device settings model with a default value of `true`.\n- Ensured it persists when settings are saved.\n\n### 2. ECMAIN Client Implementation\nUpdated the backend logic in the ECMAIN client to honor the new setting.\n\n**ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.h & .m:**\n- Added a `watchdogWDA` property to `ECBackgroundManager`.\n- Implemented persistence using `NSUserDefaults` under the key `\"EC_WATCHDOG_WDA\"`.\n- Added a public getter/setter to allow the UI or heartbeat to toggle the setting.\n\n**ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m:**\n- Modified the `sendHeartbeat:` method to check the `watchdogWDA` setting.\n- The WDA health check (probing port `10089` and `10088`) is now **skipped** if the setting is `false`.\n- This prevents the watchdog from forcefully restarting WDA when the user intentionally disables the probe.\n\n### Summary of Changes:\n- **Frontend**: Added UI checkbox for \"Watchdog WDA\".\n- **Client Core**: Added local storage for the watchdog preference.\n- **Heartbeat Logic**: Integrated the preference to conditionally skip health checks and auto-restarts of the WDA process.\n\nThe \"Watchdog WDA\" switch is now fully functional from the web control panel down to the device-level heartbeat logic.\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775209801718}}
