he getter/setter to persist this value to `NSUserDefaults`.\n    *   Update the heartbeat logic (likely in `ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m`) to wrap the WDA probe in an `if (self.watchdogWDA)` block.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"nova-fjord","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"Based on my analysis of the codebase, the \"Watchdog WDA\" switch implementation is **incomplete or missing** as per your requirements:\n\n### 1. Frontend Verification (`web_control_center/frontend/src/App.vue`)\n*   **Result:** **Not Found.**\n*   **Details:** I searched for the specific label \"探活 wda\" and the variable `watchdogWDA` within `App.vue`, but no matches were found. This suggests the checkbox has not been added to the frontend or is using different naming conventions than specified.\n\n### 2. Core Logic Verification (`ECBackgroundManager.m`)\n*   **Property & Persistence:** **Missing.**\n    *   The `watchdogWDA` property is not defined in the class extension or the implementation block of `ECBackgroundManager.m`.\n    *   There is no code in `init` or `ensureBackgroundNetworkAlive` that reads/writes a `watchdogWDA` key to `NSUserDefaults`.\n*   **Heartbeat Loop:** **Missing.**\n    *   The heartbeat logic in `ECBackgroundManager.m` (lines 1608-1683) includes a port `8089` detection for the local web server, but it does **not** contain a WDA health check or any logic to skip one based on a `watchdogWDA` flag.\n*   **Important Note:** The file imports `ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m` at the very end (line 2014). If the WDA health check logic resides in that category, it still lacks the governing property and persistence in the main manager class.\n\n### Recommendation\nTo complete the implementation, you need to:\n1.  **Frontend:** Add the `<el-checkbox v-model=\"form.watchdogWDA\">探活 wda</el-checkbox>` (or equivalent) to the `App.vue` template and initialize it in the `data()` section.\n2.  **Backend:** \n    *   Add `@property(nonatomic,