{"type":"message","id":"bc1e4d95","parentId":"ddd7279b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:50:34.694Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Identifying Missing Skills**\n\nOkay, I've confirmed `claude` is installed. After a fresh scan of `available_skills`, I saw that `coding-agent` is available, with support for `claude-code`. I'm starting to think, though, that a dedicated skill *specifically* for Claude Code might be absent, prompting more investigation.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fca57708c4c97679","name":"exec","arguments":{"workdir":"/Users/hh/Desktop/my","command":"claude --permission-mode bypassPermissions --print 'Please perform a full implementation of the \"Watchdog WDA\" switch from frontend to client-side ECMAIN. 1) In web_control_center/frontend/src/App.vue, find the device settings modal and add an <el-checkbox> for \"探活 wda\" with v-model=\"edit_form.watchdog_wda\", defaulting to true. 2) In ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.h, add @property (nonatomic, assign) BOOL watchdogWdaEnabled. 3) In ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.m, implement the setter for watchdogWdaEnabled to persist the value to NSUserDefaults using key \"EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED\". 4) In ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m, wrap the WDA heartbeat probe and restart logic (polling ports 10088 and 10089) in an if (self.watchdogWdaEnabled) block.'"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":3610,"output":258,"cacheRead":64878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68746,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775209829007,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1f51f90a-6bd4-4f61-a4e2-a23bd0ff157b"}}
