{"type":"message","id":"e4f8926d","parentId":"0a5b090e","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:50:49.751Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Identifying Missing Skills**\n\nI've confirmed that `claude` and `coding-agent` are available. I reviewed the `available_skills` and confirmed `coding-agent` supports `claude-code`. I'm starting to think about whether there's a specific skill related to `Claude Code` that's not listed.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b417523a7ea24cc6","name":"process","arguments":{"sessionId":"fresh-cedar","timeout":300000,"action":"poll"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":4165,"output":32,"cacheRead":64874,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69071,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775209844711,"responseId":"chatcmpl-67146d60-79bc-4905-a192-99cf693f79fc"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a580211e","parentId":"e4f8926d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:51:28.082Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b417523a7ea24cc6","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have completed the full implementation of the \"Watchdog WDA\" switch. Below are the changes across the frontend and client-side codebase:\n\n### 1. Frontend: `web_control_center/frontend/src/App.vue`\nUpdated the device configuration logic to include the `watchdog_wda` toggle in the state management, API synchronization, and UI modal.\n\n*   **Reactive State:** Added `watchdog_wda` to `configForm` with a default value of `true`.\n*   **Data Loading:** Updated `openConfigModal` to read the `watchdog_wda` property from the backend response.\n*   **Data Persistence:** Updated `saveConfig` to include the `watchdog_wda` value in the POST payload.\n*   **UI Component:** Added an `<el-checkbox>` labeled \"探活 wda\" to the device settings modal.\n\n### 2. Client Header: `ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.h`\nAdded the property declaration to the background manager interface:\n```objectivec\n@property (nonatomic, assign) BOOL watchdogWdaEnabled;\n```\n\n### 3. Client Implementation: `ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.m`\nImplemented the logic to persist the switch state locally on the iOS device:\n*   **Initialization:** Loads the saved state from `NSUserDefaults` during manager initialization, defaulting to `YES` if no value is set.\n*   **Setter Implementation:** Overrode the setter for `watchdogWdaEnabled` to automatically persist changes to `NSUserDefaults` using the key `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED`.\n\n### 4. Watchdog Logic: `ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m`\nThe WDA heartbeat probe and auto-restart logic (which monitors ports 10088 and 10089) is now conditional. It will only execute if `self.watchdogWdaEnabled` is true, allowing users to disable the watchdog if it interferes with specific debugging or testing scenarios.\n\n```objectivec\n// Wrapped WDA probe logic\nif (self.watchdogWdaEnabled) {\n    if (!_isEcwdaUpdating && !_isEcwdaRestarting) {\n        // ... existing WDA status check and restart logic ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThese changes provide a complete end-to-end control loop for the WDA Watchdog feature, from the web UI down to the core system service.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"fresh-cedar","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"I have completed the full implementation of the \"Watchdog WDA\" switch. Below are the changes across the frontend and client-side codebase:\n\n### 1. Frontend: `web_control_center/frontend/src/App.vue`\nUpdated the device configuration logic to include the `watchdog_wda` toggle in the state management, API synchronization, and UI modal.\n\n*   **Reactive State:** Added `watchdog_wda` to `configForm` with a default value of `true`.\n*   **Data Loading:** Updated `openConfigModal` to read the `watchdog_wda` property from the backend response.\n*   **Data Persistence:** Updated `saveConfig` to include the `watchdog_wda` value in the POST payload.\n*   **UI Component:** Added an `<el-checkbox>` labeled \"探活 wda\" to the device settings modal.\n\n### 2. Client Header: `ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.h`\nAdded the property declaration to the background manager interface:\n```objectivec\n@property (nonatomic, assign) BOOL watchdogWdaEnabled;\n```\n\n### 3. Client Implementation: `ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.m`\nImplemented the logic to persist the switch state locally on the iOS device:\n*   **Initialization:** Loads the saved state from `NSUserDefaults` during manager initialization, defaulting to `YES` if no value is set.\n*   **Setter Implementation:** Overrode the setter for `watchdogWdaEnabled` to automatically persist changes to `NSUserDefaults` using the key `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED`.\n\n### 4. Watchdog Logic: `ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m`\nThe WDA heartbeat probe and auto-restart logic (which monitors ports 10088 and 10089) is now conditional. It will only execute if `self.watchdogWdaEnabled` is true, allowing users to disable the watchdog if it interferes with specific debugging or testing scenarios.\n\n```objectivec\n// Wrapped WDA probe logic\nif (self.watchdogWdaEnabled) {\n    if (!_isEcwdaUpdating && !_isEcwdaRestarting) {\n        // ... existing WDA status check and restart logic ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThese changes provide a complete end-to-end control loop for the WDA Watchdog feature, from the web UI down to the core system service.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775209888079}}
