{"type":"message","id":"7780da91","parentId":"df615687","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:53:11.178Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_172d0380b13faf51","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have implemented the \"Watchdog WDA\" switch across both the iOS (ECMAIN) and Web Frontend components. This allows users to toggle the automatic WDA heartbeat probing and restart logic, providing more control over device stability management.\n\n### Changes Implemented\n\n#### 1. iOS Backend (ECMAIN)\n- **`ECBackgroundManager.h`**: Added the `watchdogWdaEnabled` property to the public interface.\n- **`ECBackgroundManager.m`**:\n    - **Initializer**: Now checks `NSUserDefaults` for the `\"EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED\"` key. If not found, it defaults to `YES`.\n    - **Persistent Setter**: Implemented a custom setter for `watchdogWdaEnabled` that automatically persists the value to `NSUserDefaults`, ensuring the setting survives app restarts.\n- **`ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m`**:\n    - Wrapped the entire WDA存活探测 (heartbeat probe) logic (which polls ports 10088 and 10089 and handles automatic kills/restarts) within an `if (self.watchdogWdaEnabled)` block.\n\n#### 2. Web Frontend (`App.vue`)\n- **Device Settings Modal**: Located the device settings configuration and added a new checkbox:\n    ```html\n    <el-checkbox label=\"探活 wda\" v-model=\"edit_form.watchdog_wda\" />\n    ```\n- This checkbox is bound to the `watchdog_wda` property, allowing remote control of the watchdog logic for each device.\n\n### Summary of Persistence\nThe setting is stored locally on the device using the standard iOS preference system:\n- **Key**: `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED`\n- **Default Value**: `true` (YES)\n\nAll files have been updated and saved successfully.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"warm-breeze","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"I have implemented the \"Watchdog WDA\" switch across both the iOS (ECMAIN) and Web Frontend components. This allows users to toggle the automatic WDA heartbeat probing and restart logic, providing more control over device stability management.\n\n### Changes Implemented\n\n#### 1. iOS Backend (ECMAIN)\n- **`ECBackgroundManager.h`**: Added the `watchdogWdaEnabled` property to the public interface.\n- **`ECBackgroundManager.m`**:\n    - **Initializer**: Now checks `NSUserDefaults` for the `\"EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED\"` key. If not found, it defaults to `YES`.\n    - **Persistent Setter**: Implemented a custom setter for `watchdogWdaEnabled` that automatically persists the value to `NSUserDefaults`, ensuring the setting survives app restarts.\n- **`ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m`**:\n    - Wrapped the entire WDA存活探测 (heartbeat probe) logic (which polls ports 10088 and 10089 and handles automatic kills/restarts) within an `if (self.watchdogWdaEnabled)` block.\n\n#### 2. Web Frontend (`App.vue`)\n- **Device Settings Modal**: Located the device settings configuration and added a new checkbox:\n    ```html\n    <el-checkbox label=\"探活 wda\" v-model=\"edit_form.watchdog_wda\" />\n    ```\n- This checkbox is bound to the `watchdog_wda` property, allowing remote control of the watchdog logic for each device.\n\n### Summary of Persistence\nThe setting is stored locally on the device using the standard iOS preference system:\n- **Key**: `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED`\n- **Default Value**: `true` (YES)\n\nAll files have been updated and saved successfully.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775209991176}}
