{"type":"message","id":"2bf4bc53","parentId":"c111b316","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:58:17.741Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a33ade7745a518dd","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have completed the full implementation of the \"Watchdog WDA\" switch. Here is the summary of the changes made and verified:\n\n### 1. Frontend Implementation (`web_control_center/frontend/src/App.vue`)\nAdded the checkbox to the settings modal to allow users to toggle the WDA watchdog feature.\n```vue\n<el-checkbox label=\"探活 wda\" v-model=\"edit_form.watchdog_wda\" />\n```\n\n### 2. Backend Interface (`ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.h`)\nDefined the property in the `ECBackgroundManager` interface.\n```objectivec\n@property (nonatomic, assign) BOOL watchdogWdaEnabled;\n```\n\n### 3. Persistance Logic (`ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.m`)\nImplemented the setter to persist the configuration to `NSUserDefaults` and initialized the value during the manager's startup.\n- **Key**: `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED`\n- **Default**: `YES`\n\n### 4. Heartbeat Integration (`ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m`)\nWrapped the WDA heartbeat probe and auto-restart logic in a conditional block that respects the user's setting. The \"Watchdog\" probe (checking ports 10088/10089 and restarting the WDA service) will now only execute if `self.watchdogWdaEnabled` is `YES`.\n\n### Verification\nI have verified that all files were correctly saved and contain the expected implementation. The toggle state is now fully synchronized from the web dashboard to the iOS background management system.\n\n- `ECBackgroundManager.h:25`\n- `ECBackgroundManager.m:89-94, 194-200`\n- `ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m:104` (Logic wrapped in `if (self.watchdogWdaEnabled)`)\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"lucky-forest","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"I have completed the full implementation of the \"Watchdog WDA\" switch. Here is the summary of the changes made and verified:\n\n### 1. Frontend Implementation (`web_control_center/frontend/src/App.vue`)\nAdded the checkbox to the settings modal to allow users to toggle the WDA watchdog feature.\n```vue\n<el-checkbox label=\"探活 wda\" v-model=\"edit_form.watchdog_wda\" />\n```\n\n### 2. Backend Interface (`ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.h`)\nDefined the property in the `ECBackgroundManager` interface.\n```objectivec\n@property (nonatomic, assign) BOOL watchdogWdaEnabled;\n```\n\n### 3. Persistance Logic (`ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.m`)\nImplemented the setter to persist the configuration to `NSUserDefaults` and initialized the value during the manager's startup.\n- **Key**: `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED`\n- **Default**: `YES`\n\n### 4. Heartbeat Integration (`ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m`)\nWrapped the WDA heartbeat probe and auto-restart logic in a conditional block that respects the user's setting. The \"Watchdog\" probe (checking ports 10088/10089 and restarting the WDA service) will now only execute if `self.watchdogWdaEnabled` is `YES`.\n\n### Verification\nI have verified that all files were correctly saved and contain the expected implementation. The toggle state is now fully synchronized from the web dashboard to the iOS background management system.\n\n- `ECBackgroundManager.h:25`\n- `ECBackgroundManager.m:89-94, 194-200`\n- `ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m:104` (Logic wrapped in `if (self.watchdogWdaEnabled)`)\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775210297738}}
