ts?\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"rapid-cloud","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"I have completed the analysis of `App.vue` to relocate the **Watchdog WDA** (探活 wda) switch from the configuration modal to the main dashboard.\n\n### 🔍 Discovery Summary\n- **Current Location**: The switch is located at line 4372 within a `grid` in the configuration modal, bound to `configForm.watchdog_wda`.\n- **Target Dashboard Area**: I have identified the main device rendering loop at line 3461, which uses `v-for=\"dev in sortedDevices\"`. This renders a table-like view for each device.\n- **Secondary View**: There is also a \"Batch Device\" card-based view starting at line 4192.\n\n### 🛠️ Implementation Plan\n1.  **Remove from Modal**: I will remove the `el-form-item` containing the \"探活 wda\" checkbox from lines 4372-4374.\n2.  **Add to Device Card/Row**: I will insert a more compact version of the toggle into the `sortedDevices` table row (likely in a \"Status\" or \"Actions\" column) and/or into the batch device cards at line 4193.\n3.  **Update State Binding**: The binding will change from the global `configForm.watchdog_wda` to a per-device property `dev.watchdog_wda`. This ensures that toggling the watchdog for one device does not affect others.\n4.  **Sync with Backend**: I will ensure that the toggle triggers an API call (likely via a `toggleWatchdog` method) to persist the change to the backend `database.py` and `device_manager.py`.\n\n### 📋 Updated Todo List\n- [x] Analyze `App.vue` to locate the switch and dashboard areas\n- [ ] Move the switch from the modal to the `sortedDevices` table and device cards\n- [ ] Update state binding to `dev.watchdog_wda`\n- [ ] Implement/Verify the backend sync method for per-device toggling\n\nI am now ready to apply these changes to the codebase. Would you like me to proceed with the specific line edits?\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775211377664}}
