d. This ensures the \"watchdog\" state is persisted immediately without needing to open the full configuration modal.\n\n2.  **Main Status Table Updates**:\n    *   **Header**: Added a new \"探活\" column header to the main device table.\n    *   **Row**: Integrated an `<el-switch size=\"small\">` into each device row, bound to `dev.watchdog_wda`.\n\n3.  **Slave Matrix Updates**:\n    *   Added the same small toggle switch to the header of each device card in the \"Slave Matrix\" (从属矩阵) view, allowing for quick control during group operations.\n\n4.  **Configuration Modal Cleanup**:\n    *   Removed the redundant \"探活 wda\" checkbox from the device configuration modal to streamline the interface and prevent conflicting update paths.\n\nThese changes provide a much faster way to enable or disable WDA connection monitoring directly from the primary monitoring interface.\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775211506823}}
