\n2.  **ECBackgroundManager.m**: Synchronized the background manager to use the **shared App Group defaults** (`group.com.ecmain.shared`) instead of standard defaults. This ensures that the switch state in the UI and the watchdog logic in the background are always in sync.\n3.  **ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m**: Verified that the WDA heartbeat probe (port 10088) and its auto-restart logic are wrapped within the `self.watchdogWdaEnabled` property check.\n\n### Verification:\n*   **Default State**: On a fresh install or if the setting hasn't been touched, the \"Watchdog WDA\" switch will now be **ON** by default.\n*   **Status Probing**: I confirmed that in `ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m`, the logic specifically checks `watchdogWdaEnabled`. If the user toggles the switch to **OFF**, the code will skip the port 10088 probe and will not attempt to restart WDA, fulfilling the requirement that no status probing or restarting takes place when disabled.\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775212038716}}
