{"type":"message","id":"25dd3dc2","parentId":"484ea1a5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:28:40.142Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3927ecc9da940c90","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have updated **ECBackgroundManager.m** to ensure the \"Watchdog WDA\" switch correctly uses the shared App Group container (`group.com.ecmain.shared`) for persistence, ensuring consistency across different process contexts and system reboots.\n\n### Key Changes Implemented:\n\n1.  **Shared Persistence**: Modified `init` and `setWatchdogWdaEnabled:` to use `[[NSUserDefaults alloc] initWithSuiteName:@\"group.com.ecmain.shared\"]` instead of standard defaults.\n2.  **Default Value Enforcement**: Ensured the `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED` key defaults to `YES` (enabled) if it has never been set.\n3.  **Heartbeat Integration**: Verified that `ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m` consumes this property. When enabled, the background manager now actively probes the WDA status on port `10088`:\n    *   **Level 1 Failure**: Attempts to relaunch the process.\n    *   **Level 2 Failure**: Performs a `SIGKILL` on the runner and executes a clean restart to resolve sub-thread stalls.\n\n### Verified Persistence Logic:\n\n```objectivec\n// In ECBackgroundManager.m\n- (void)setWatchdogWdaEnabled:(BOOL)watchdogWdaEnabled {\n    _watchdogWdaEnabled = watchdogWdaEnabled;\n    NSUserDefaults *defaults = [[NSUserDefaults alloc] initWithSuiteName:@\"group.com.ecmain.shared\"];\n    [defaults setBool:watchdogWdaEnabled forKey:@\"EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED\"];\n    [defaults synchronize];\n}\n```\n\nThe implementation is now fully synchronized with the background heartbeat watchdog, providing robust stability governance for the WDA service.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"sharp-pine","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"I have updated **ECBackgroundManager.m** to ensure the \"Watchdog WDA\" switch correctly uses the shared App Group container (`group.com.ecmain.shared`) for persistence, ensuring consistency across different process contexts and system reboots.\n\n### Key Changes Implemented:\n\n1.  **Shared Persistence**: Modified `init` and `setWatchdogWdaEnabled:` to use `[[NSUserDefaults alloc] initWithSuiteName:@\"group.com.ecmain.shared\"]` instead of standard defaults.\n2.  **Default Value Enforcement**: Ensured the `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED` key defaults to `YES` (enabled) if it has never been set.\n3.  **Heartbeat Integration**: Verified that `ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m` consumes this property. When enabled, the background manager now actively probes the WDA status on port `10088`:\n    *   **Level 1 Failure**: Attempts to relaunch the process.\n    *   **Level 2 Failure**: Performs a `SIGKILL` on the runner and executes a clean restart to resolve sub-thread stalls.\n\n### Verified Persistence Logic:\n\n```objectivec\n// In ECBackgroundManager.m\n- (void)setWatchdogWdaEnabled:(BOOL)watchdogWdaEnabled {\n    _watchdogWdaEnabled = watchdogWdaEnabled;\n    NSUserDefaults *defaults = [[NSUserDefaults alloc] initWithSuiteName:@\"group.com.ecmain.shared\"];\n    [defaults setBool:watchdogWdaEnabled forKey:@\"EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED\"];\n    [defaults synchronize];\n}\n```\n\nThe implementation is now fully synchronized with the background heartbeat watchdog, providing robust stability governance for the WDA service.\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775212120139}}
