{"type":"message","id":"b976a27d","parentId":"ced466a8","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:30:58.652Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"大圣，搞定了！我已经确保了“探活 WDA”的默认状态和逻辑。\n\n### 🛠️ 修改细节：\n\n1.  **默认状态 (ON)**：\n    *   我修改了 `ViewController.m` 的 `viewDidLoad` 逻辑。如果是首次安装或者该配置项不存在，它会自动将 `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED` 设置为 `YES`。\n    *   **iOS 界面显示**：你打开 App 仪表盘，开关默认就是开启（选中）状态。\n2.  **双端同步 (Data Sync)**：\n    *   之前发现 background manager 读的是标准 defaults 而 UI 写的是 shared suite，导致逻辑没同步。\n    *   **已修复**：现在 `ECBackgroundManager.m` 的 `init` 和 `setter` 全部统一使用 `group.com.ecmain.shared` 这一共享套件。你在 UI 上拨动开关，后台逻辑会**秒级同步**。\n3.  **探活逻辑判定**：\n    *   在 `ECBackgroundManager_Heartbeat.m` 中，我确认了核心代码：`if (self.watchdogWdaEnabled && ...)`。\n    *   **效果**：如果开关被用户手动关闭，ECMAIN 会彻底**跳过**对 10088 端口的状态探测，也绝对不会主动拉起或重启 ECWDA。\n\n### 🚀 编译完成：\n*   **版本号**：更新至 `#1784 (Auto)`。\n*   **编译报告**：全量编译成功 (`BUILD SUCCEEDED`)，最新的 `ecmain.tar` 已同步到后端。\n\n现在的机制完全符合你的要求：默认开启保活，用户关闭后彻底静默。你可以放心测试了！🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":83541,"output":393,"cacheRead":24237,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108171,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775212252867,"responseId":"chatcmpl-bac4ac15-1853-4a4d-9aa2-6d33d4379bb4"}}
{"type":"compaction","id":"e32d2b54","parentId":"b976a27d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:32:39.811Z","summary":"## Goal\nThe user is developing and optimizing an iOS automation and device management framework (internal name \"EC\"). The primary focus is improving connection stability between the web control center and iOS devices, implementing robust mutual watchdogs between system components, and providing UI controls for these features.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- **Tools**: Preference for using `claude-code` CLI for deep code analysis and modifications.\n- **Workflow**: Non-interactive execution for Claude Code via `--permission-mode bypassPermissions --print`.\n- **UI Labels**: Specific Chinese terminology used for UI elements (e.g., \"探活 wda\").\n- **Persona**: AI assistant uses the persona \"龙虾\" (Lobster) and refers to the user as \"大圣\" (Great Sage).\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Analyzed project structure in `/Users/hh/Desktop/my` (iOS WDA customization, ECMAIN engine, Web Control Center).\n- [x] Cleaned up repository logs, temporary test scripts, and build artifacts.\n- [x] Optimized Backend WebSocket stability: Implemented active heartbeats (30s ping/10s pong), handshake timeouts, and explicit socket closure on reconnection in `web_control_center/backend/main.py`.\n- [x] Optimized iOS Client WebSocket: Implemented exponential backoff reconnection (1s to 30s) in `ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.m`.\n- [x] Implemented two-way Watchdog: Added a reciprocal health check in `WebDriverAgentLib/Categories/XCUIDevice+FBHealthCheck.m` where ECWDA monitors and relaunches ECMAIN.\n- [x] Added \"Watchdog WDA\" toggle: Implemented backend support and per-device configuration persistence.\n- [x] Relocated UI Toggle: Moved the \"探活 wda\" switch from the config modal to the main dashboard (device list table and grid cards) in `web_control_center/frontend/src/App.vue` for immediate access and instant API persistence via `updateWatchdog(dev)`.\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Verification of the final dashboard UI changes by the user.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Two-way Watchdog**: Decided to have ECWDA monitor ECMAIN via port 8089 to ensure system resilience if the main manager app crashes/hangs.\n- **Dashboard Integration**: Moved the watchdog toggle to the main dashboard so users can disable auto-restarts of WDA during manual debugging without opening nested menus.\n- **Instant Persistence**: Implemented `updateWatchdog` to trigger a `POST` request immediately on switch change instead of waiting for a global \"Save\" button.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Rebuild **ECMAIN** (`python3 build_full.py`) and **ECWDA** (`python3 build_wda.py`) to apply the new watchdog logic.\n2. Deploy the updated IPAs to devices and verify the exponential backoff and mutual restart behavior.\n3. Observe dashboard toggle functionality to ensure per-device settings are correctly synchronized to the iOS `NSUserDefaults`.\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Project Root**: `/Users/hh/Desktop/my`\n- **Build Commands** (stored in `TOOLS.md`):\n    - ECMAIN: `python3 build_full.py`\n    - ECWDA: `python3 build_wda.py`\n- **Watchdog Logic**:\n    - ECMAIN monitors ECWDA on port 10088 / 10089.\n    - ECWDA monitors ECMAIN on port 8089.\n    - Setting key in iOS `NSUserDefaults`: `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED`.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user reported that the \"Watchdog WDA\" (探活 WDA) switch was still missing from the dashboard of the **ecmain** iOS application. They requested that the assistant locate the dashboard code and add the switch alongside existing controls like \"Independent WDA Restart.\"\n\n## Early Progress\n- **Implementation**: Used a coding agent to modify `ViewController.m` in the ECMAIN project. \n- **UI Elements**: Added a `UISwitch` and a \"探活 WDA:\" label to the main dashboard interface.\n- **Persistence**: Bound the switch state to `NSUserDefaults` (suite: `group.com.ecmain.shared`, key: `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED`) so the setting persists across app launches.\n- **Layout Management**: Adjusted the vertical offsets (`y` coordinates) of subsequent UI elements (metadata labels and account lists) to ensure the new switch does not overlap with existing content.\n- **Verification**: Programmatically verified that the code changes were correctly applied and followed the project's established UI patterns.\n\n## Context for Suffix\nAfter implementing the fix, the assistant initiated a full build process using `python3 build_full.py` to ensure the changes were integrated correctly. The retained suffix contains the build logs, including compiler warnings for unrelated parts of the codebase.","firstKeptEntryId":"afda8f54","tokensBefore":108171,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":false}
