{"type":"message","id":"1befe9d6","parentId":"c6832d76","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:32:51.438Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Assessing Stability of WebSockets**\n\nI've successfully implemented active heartbeats (30s ping/10s pong) in the backend's web_control_center to ensure WebSocket stability. This proactive approach should address potential connection drops and improve reliability. The \"EC\" project is progressing nicely in that regard.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9ccb9904669d1967","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"\n## Project \"EC\" (iOS Automation Framework)\n- **WebSocket Stability**: \n    - Backend: Added active heartbeats (30s/10s) and handshake timeouts in `web_control_center/backend/main.py`.\n    - iOS Client: Implemented exponential backoff (1s-30s) for reconnect logic in `ECMAIN/ECMAIN/Core/ECBackgroundManager.m`.\n- **Mutual Watchdog**:\n    - **Logic**: ECWDA (WebDriverAgent) monitors ECMAIN on port 8089; ECMAIN monitors ECWDA on port 10088/10089.\n    - **Control**: Added \"Watchdog WDA\" (探活 WDA) toggle to both the Web Control Center dashboard and the ECMAIN iOS app home screen.\n    - **Persistence**: Used `NSUserDefaults` (Suite: `group.com.ecmain.shared`, Key: `EC_WATCHDOG_WDA_ENABLED`).\n    - **Default State**: Enabled (YES) by default unless manually toggled off. \n- **Build Progress**: Latest ECMAIN build succeeded (#1784).\n","file":"memory/2026-04-03.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":1758,"output":287,"cacheRead":8142,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":10187,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775212365334,"responseId":"chatcmpl-bf28d142-9145-4be8-9722-1cdc0c962aae"}}
