{"type":"message","id":"601df10b","parentId":"3961dfbb","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:41:53.775Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Investigating Network Loss**\n\nI'm focusing on why `ecmain` loses network connectivity shortly after the iOS device's screen turns off. No location services are involved. My current hypothesis is that the OS is aggressively shutting down network processes in the background. I'm exploring potential solutions to maintain the network connection, such as background task configurations and network-related entitlements.\n\n\n**Refining Background Processes**\n\nI've been working to optimize background processes. I've removed the `location` background mode as requested. I'm tweaking the WebSocket heartbeat/ping, reducing the ping frequency and reconnect delay. Furthermore, I'm enhancing the audio keep-alive by confirming the proper `AVAudioSession` category and ensuring `ECKeepAlive` activates correctly on background entry. I plan to implement `beginBackgroundTaskWithExpirationHandler`.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3c56497c15fc08c9","name":"process","arguments":{"timeout":480000,"action":"poll","sessionId":"gentle-ridge"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":88683,"output":32,"cacheRead":8154,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96869,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775212908253,"responseId":"chatcmpl-b68368d8-24a0-4785-8dbf-e34ac7df42d5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7ca007b1","parentId":"601df10b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:42:20.100Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3c56497c15fc08c9","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have optimized the **ECMAIN** background keep-alive system and completely removed all location-based services as requested. Here is a summary of the changes:\n\n### 1. Removal of Location Services\n*   **`Info.plist`**: Removed the `location` string from the `UIBackgroundModes` array.\n*   **`ECBackgroundManager.h`**: Removed the `isLocationActive` property and the `toggleLocation:` method declaration.\n*   **`ECBackgroundManager.m`**: \n    *   Removed `CLLocationManager` property and related delegate conformance.\n    *   Completely deleted the `toggleLocation:` implementation and the `didUpdateLocations` delegate method.\n    *   Cleaned up all internal state flags related to location.\n\n### 2. WebSocket Connectivity Optimization\n*   **Aggressive Heartbeat**: Changed the WebSocket Ping timer interval from **30 seconds to 15 seconds** to better maintain connections on unstable networks.\n*   **Faster Recovery**: Changed the WebSocket reconnection delay from **60 seconds to 10 seconds** across all failure handlers (disconnects, timeouts, and DNS errors).\n\n### 3. Background Task & Audio Enhancement\n*   **Extra Execution Time**: Updated `ensureBackgroundNetworkAlive` to use `beginBackgroundTaskWithExpirationHandler`. This explicitly tells iOS to grant the app additional background time (with a 5-second buffer) whenever it enters the background, facilitating reliable network synchronization.\n*   **Audio Persistence**: Confirmed and updated the `AVAudioSession` configuration to use `AVAudioSessionCategoryPlayAndRecord` with `MixWithOthers` and `AllowBluetooth`. This ensures the microphone keep-alive remains active without interrupting other apps' audio or being paused by the system.\n\n### 4. Verification\nA global search (`Grep`) confirms that no references to `locationManager` or `CLLocationManager` remain in the codebase, ensuring total removal of location-tracking dependencies.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"gentle-ridge","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"I have optimized the **ECMAIN** background keep-alive system and completely removed all location-based services as requested. Here is a summary of the changes:\n\n### 1. Removal of Location Services\n*   **`Info.plist`**: Removed the `location` string from the `UIBackgroundModes` array.\n*   **`ECBackgroundManager.h`**: Removed the `isLocationActive` property and the `toggleLocation:` method declaration.\n*   **`ECBackgroundManager.m`**: \n    *   Removed `CLLocationManager` property and related delegate conformance.\n    *   Completely deleted the `toggleLocation:` implementation and the `didUpdateLocations` delegate method.\n    *   Cleaned up all internal state flags related to location.\n\n### 2. WebSocket Connectivity Optimization\n*   **Aggressive Heartbeat**: Changed the WebSocket Ping timer interval from **30 seconds to 15 seconds** to better maintain connections on unstable networks.\n*   **Faster Recovery**: Changed the WebSocket reconnection delay from **60 seconds to 10 seconds** across all failure handlers (disconnects, timeouts, and DNS errors).\n\n### 3. Background Task & Audio Enhancement\n*   **Extra Execution Time**: Updated `ensureBackgroundNetworkAlive` to use `beginBackgroundTaskWithExpirationHandler`. This explicitly tells iOS to grant the app additional background time (with a 5-second buffer) whenever it enters the background, facilitating reliable network synchronization.\n*   **Audio Persistence**: Confirmed and updated the `AVAudioSession` configuration to use `AVAudioSessionCategoryPlayAndRecord` with `MixWithOthers` and `AllowBluetooth`. This ensures the microphone keep-alive remains active without interrupting other apps' audio or being paused by the system.\n\n### 4. Verification\nA global search (`Grep`) confirms that no references to `locationManager` or `CLLocationManager` remain in the codebase, ensuring total removal of location-tracking dependencies.\n","name":"claude bypassPermissions"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775212940097}}
{"type":"message","id":"1ae1bb07","parentId":"7ca007b1","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:42:25.331Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Investigating Network Loss**\n\nI'm focusing on why `ecmain` loses network connectivity shortly after the iOS device's screen turns off. No location services are involved. My current hypothesis is that the OS is aggressively shutting down network processes in the background. I'm exploring potential solutions to maintain the network connection, such as background task configurations and network-related entitlements.\n\n\n**Refining Background Processes**\n\nI'm now prioritizing optimizations to background processes. Specifically, I've removed the 'location' background mode, as requested. Next, I'm adjusting WebSocket ping and heartbeat frequencies for mobile network resilience. I'm also ensuring the audio keep-alive mechanism, including silent audio playback, is robust, and finally implementing `beginBackgroundTaskWithExpirationHandler` to handle background task limitations.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c1e36853acd87ac4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 build_full.py","workdir":"/Users/hh/Desktop/my"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":80686,"output":34,"cacheRead":16308,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97028,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775212940101,"responseId":"chatcmpl-82cfc1b4-aeef-465f-b27c-ce757bb8e495"}}
