{"type":"message","id":"4cfb1a1b","parentId":"91dfc763","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:42:41.804Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing Network Drops**\n\nI'm currently investigating reports of `ecmain` losing network connectivity shortly after the iOS device's screen turns off. My primary goal is to maintain `ecmain`'s active network connection, even when the device is locked. A significant constraint is the complete absence of location data in this process.\n\n\n**Refining Keep-Alive Strategy**\n\nI've made progress refining the keep-alive strategy. The `location` background mode is removed from `Info.plist`, as instructed. Now, I'm focusing on WebSocket and audio optimizations. Specifically, I've adjusted the WebSocket heartbeat and ping frequencies. I'm also ensuring the audio session is correctly configured, and confirming the `ECKeepAlive` silent audio starts properly upon background entry. I'm also working on implementing `beginBackgroundTaskWithExpirationHandler`.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_438927900837eef4","name":"process","arguments":{"timeout":600000,"action":"poll","sessionId":"mild-shell"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":58169,"output":31,"cacheRead":24439,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82639,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775212955369,"responseId":"chatcmpl-35976b37-dd28-4145-8266-b9b7d6592d07"}}
